# Cline Rules — Phaser Survivor Game

## Language
- Always respond and comment in English

## Code Style
- Use vanilla JavaScript (no TypeScript)
- Use ES6 modules (import/export)
- Prefer const over let where possible
- No semicolons optional — but be consistent throughout the project

## Project Structure
- Entry point: src/main.js
- Game config: src/config.js
- Scenes go in: src/scenes/
- Game entities (Player, Enemy, etc.) go in: src/entities/
- Utility/helper functions go in: src/utils/
- Never dump everything into a single file

## Phaser Specifics
- Use Phaser 3 (installed via npm)
- Use Phaser.Scene class extensions for all scenes
- Keep physics, input, and rendering logic inside the scene or entity it belongs to
- Use Phaser's arcade physics for movement and collision

## How to Work
- Make one focused change at a time — don't refactor unrelated code while adding features
- If a file gets longer than ~200 lines, suggest splitting it
- Don't add features I haven't asked for
- If something is unclear, ask before writing code — don't guess and produce a lot of wrong code
- Prefer small, testable steps over big rewrites

## What to Avoid
- No TypeScript
- No CSS frameworks (this is a canvas game)
- Don't install unnecessary packages
- Don't rewrite working code unless I explicitly ask